caption: I'll punch any of the people complaining about their cook or their service or whatever in these reviews.  These amazing people have came through for me with the best soups while I was sick the past 2 days. I mentioned I was sick on the phone and they included a GINGER SHOT for me! They did not have to but they did and I appreciate it. Never had bad food from here, a vegan must try. Thank you loving hut <3

I decided after months of holding out.... I would try again. I paid for two extra Roti Breads as I was splitting the soup with someone else. Not only was the roti bread extra greasy, there was only one and that’s happened 3 times so far that I can remember. The soup wasn’t spicy 😩 and the bread was nasty. I don’t know what happened to the last cook but bring him back! I feel like you got some guy that used to make Frank’s on the corner to take the job and it’s not the same! Anyway, I’m so disappointed I refuse to ever try again. Everyone at the office feels the same.  The owner is really nice; sir, you have to get a new cook.
I waited almost an hour for my takeout order.  Exceptionally lousy customer service.  I kept having the remind the young man at the counter what I ordered.  The food was overly salty.  Never again!

Overpriced for nothing,the general joes delight was terrible batter seemed old and not crispy at all, it was so gummy and soft also had a hint of fishy smell  I asked for white rice and they gave me brown/purple!!  The sweet and sour delight has a bad greasy flavor and they didn’t even toss it in the sauce. They gave me the sauce on the side when I did not ask for that, sauce had like five carrot slices and a few pineapple chunk’s  The hot and sour soap was not spicy at all nor sour tasted like a mixture of wonton and plain veggie broth. I got to the end of the bowl and had nothing but sesame oil. Wanted so badly for it to taste good smh  Rangoos were decent.  I hav been vegan for  7 years, I would be embarrassed to bring my non vegan friends here. Very disheartening.  I have been to many loving hut locations from Florida to New York this was the worst one.

Had a great experience here. The service was really good and the food was delicious. Our waiter  was really friendly and attentive. He made sure we got everything we needed and made us feel very comfortable. We ordered a few appetizers & entrees and they all came out very quickly. The food was absolutely delicious and all the sauces was super tasty. Will definitely be back!
Got the wrong seitan sandwich (I think? No avocado), and it was brutal. People eat that? :|

Highly disappointed. I ordered the teriyaki soy and what I got was a leaking container of what it seemed to be sweet and sour sauce with whatever meat I was afraid to eat. The cutlets were bright pink, which I have never seen before, did not taste like the regular soy I get at other asian cuisines. And the sauce wasn't even teriyaki. I took a few bits and had to stop. The donut was really good but I was surprised at how terrible the main food was. Will never order from there again, go to a different vegan asian restaurant. Wish I spent my money elsewhere.

I was disappointed. I ordered the general Tao chicken which looked at least half broccoli and half chicken but it turns out it was pretty much all fried chicken. The portions are big but I didn’t want big portions of just fried chicken. Definitely would have liked more broccoli!
Excellent
In Loving hut, I had  my best experience in food. really loving it.  Thanks for the discount. Will visit again.
Really great food, better service.  Found my new fav!
Got some food to go tasted great and was packed well. 🍩 s are good too!
Mm     Great food and kind owner.
It's  good restaurant,  very well,I'll be back.
both my kids and i always order the sweet and sour divine- double check your takeout order

Not going to mince words. The food here is BAD. I came here with my sister and ordered a variety of dishes. Fried mushrooms, that’s hard to mess up and they were flavorless and hard. Wonton Soup tasted like hot dog water, edamame was half rotten, and the pad Thai was a soggy mess. We sent all of it back, barely touched (it was also cold which was weird). They said they would not take it off just because we didn’t like it and didn’t eat it, that’s their policy. They only refunded the edamame because it was visibly rotten. I could have argued more but I just didn’t care enough. Everyone there had a terrible attitude. Definitely will not go back. I’ll hit Modern Brooklyn, JaJaJa or Chloe’s instead.

Not sure how dinning in food tastes, but delivery is pretty awful. First off, the food is always somewhat cold or old tasting and makes me feel sluggish and kinda gross after eating. However, The fried king oyster mushrooms are somewhat enjoyable, but everything else doesn’t have much flavor, and the falafel salad is a no go. .Ordered twice just to see if i misjudged the first time, being vegan in nyc gives you plenty of options. But to be frank, perhaps this place has way too much going on in their menu to keep track of perfecting each cuisine and providing the appropriate flavor.  If you don’t care about flavor eat here, if you want your money’s worth of food and flavor, eat some place else.

My co-workers and I used to love this place. My favorite dish was the Malaysian curry stew. I had to wait over an hour for my order today, it was complete garbage. The vegetable soup was packed wrong and spilled out and burned me, then the malaysian curry stew was cooked wrong; it wasn't even liquid it had a consistency of jello but it was hot - What? Then the Roti bread was so saturated in oil, I refused consume it. I never received the spring rolls and waited over an hour for my order AND IT WAS A PICK UP! I didn't notice the spring rolls were missing bc they made me late to return to work from lunch so I had to get out of there. When I called to complain, they gave me such a hard time. The person that answered was so rude. They said there's a new chef.. Well he can't cook and I'm never going back now! I was actually excited for lunch and waited until almost 5pm... For the food to go in the TRASH!
Idk if it's me, but the Koren BBQ sauce tasted like nail polish remover. I wasn't really into any of the food.
Pad Thai was watery and general tso was flavorless and chewy and the rice portion was small for what is cost.
Highly recommend restaurant in Brooklyn 🥰🌱
the worse restaurant, the woman (host) don't have manners, very rude and the food very disgusting ,
I love this place! There are volumes of menu items. Everything is Vegan. The food quality is always fresh and tasty
This food was so horrible. I got a variety of different options, but the food tasted old, frozen, and microwaved. Don’t waste your money here.
One of my go to delivery spots. The General Tso's is what I get a lot of the time and it’s always great!
Awesome place for people with high cholesterol!!!!!!! Extremely recommended.
Loved it a lot! So many options, nice portions,  lovely staff! Highly recommended!
Ordered through Door Dash. Got the Avocado Taco 🌮 , Facon Cheese Burger 🍔 and Fries. And a Vegan 🌱 Donut 🍩. Hands down the Best food I’ve had in NY so far and I’m not even a vegan.
My family and I use to go here a lot. We normally did the buffet which was always very good. The staff were always friendly to my family even when my children were not at their best behavior.
Tasty vegan food with a huge menu. Great takeout
Loving Hut is open for Takeout and Delivery every day, 12PM–10PM during COVID.  It seems they deliver with DoorDash, Postmates, and delivery.com.
Ordered not too long ago, but receptionist was extremely rude and hung up on me multiple times. I asked her very simply and politey on the status of my order. Extremely rude and inconsiderate.

Every time i come into this establishment, the staff is friendly and knowledgeable. Come in for the happy hour. Really get the most bang for your buck. Lots of tasty options. The “chicken” is always crispy. They understand flavor, texture and contrast. I always gravitate towards the General Tso Chicken Combo platter. Come and check these guys out if you’re ever in bushwick / East Williamsburg area!
Love to see a cruelty free food establishment and thoroughly enjoyed it highly recommended and thank you for supplying food that wasn’t slaughtered all the best
Vegan food and Awesome Sweets by Vegatreats !!
Fully flavored and healthy
Incredible food that’s good for you too! what’s not to love about that? :)
One of the best vegetarian restaurants in NY.

I'm not vegetarian, but I LOVE it here and always come back. I've had their classic burgers, yuca/ sweet potato fries, falafel salad, seaweed salad, roti breads, Thai tea, and I've enjoyed everything. The only dish I wasn't a big fan of was the mac and cheese. It wasn't bad, just different ( because its its obviously not cheese). I highely recommend Loving Hut to everyone. I will give it a 5 star once the flies are controlled though....for now, Ill order to go.

HIGHLY DISAPPOINTED!  ordered food from here and waited a whole hour for it to be delivered. Then, my food comes and it is ICE cold. My fries were not fully cooked and they were drenched in oil. Not to mention, I found a rubber band in my french fries and it was yellow. I had requested sides which I didn't get. Not a pleasant experience!  NEVER ORDERING FROM HERE EVER AGAIN!!!!!!!
2/14/2020 here for the first time...had the General Tso’s and the ginger tea...big thumbs up 👍👍

Very tasty food and friendly service. A gem!
I haven't ordered a lot but the foods not amazing just pretty decent. Yuka fries could be better and maybe a new choice of bread. Overall it was decent

I've frequented Loving Hut for a few years and it's mad decent. Cute little spot, conveniently located right off the L train. However, I normally resort to ordering from Seamless or Uber Eats as the waitresses the past several times I've dined in were uncomfortably condescending and aloof. As someone who gives regular business and tips well, this is a big put-off.
Always 45-60 minutes late with delivery. It’s an ongoing problem that they either don’t care about or cannot figure out how to solve.
Vegan food made with love and great taste!!!
Food fresh and very tasty
Great food, great service

I placed an order at 11pm. They are supposed to deliver until 11:30. They called me to tell me they were out of the soysage and gave me another option. They told me the order would be delivered by 1145. At 11:50 I called the restaurant several times and there was no answer. I then received a call from seamless saying that the order had been cancelled because the driver got a flat tire. Just change the delivery option if you don’t want to deliver so late. I was starving and it was only vegan option. I always have a great experience with them in restaurant and with delivery but this was not cool.
Wide variety of dishes that are all deliciously creative!

Weird things are ghosts. None of them here. Turmpet music was loadmusic. Ear area iSnt hurting me any. More! Tried to make a dance for the folks but I feeled Down. Wished for onions ring tho love all the five starship! Rock out!

Had a great experience here. The service was really good and the food was delicious. Our waiter (tall blonde guy with long hair) was really friendly and attentive. He made sure we got everything we needed and made us feel very comfortable. We ordered a few appetizers & entrees and they all came out very quickly. The food was absolutely delicious and all the sauces was super tasty. Will definitely be back!

Wow. I ordered the eggplants with asparagus and it was very tasty.
Burger was pretty good. Would eat again. But the mac and cheese is some of the worst food I've ever eaten. STAY AWAY FROM THE MAC AND CHEESE

Love coming here. I am not vegan, but I completely enjoy many things from here. The loving hut burger is absolutely my favorite thing. I don't know what they put in that burger, but I get it EVERY. SINGLE. TIME. My favorite thing about it is that it isn't that fake meat substitution stuff, and it is actually made with oatmeal (i think?) and kale, and it is just amazing. I often get the samosas which is always made so well, and the sauce for it is perfect. The prices and portions you get are extremely decent. I could go on and on. I often come for pickup, and have had some issues with not getting everything I ordered (I had to walk back and get it), or one the of delivery guys took my pickup order by accident ( I had to wait pretty long that time), but the staff is always kind and apologizes. Just don't go when you are in a rush :). The desserts they have are also great (they don't make it there, so a little pricey)! I always pick up a cake when I am craving something sweet. Thanks for being great!
Zero stars. Food had roaches in it. They denied it and wouldn't refund me.
The service was friendly and great. The food was delicious. Great flavors and portions
It's always a pleasure to visit this restaurant, their food is great, and their service is wonderful. I have no complaints.
Been visiting the loving hut for a few years now and somehow always forget to post how lovely this place is.  The curry noodles are a bit spicy but one of my favorite along with the Thai iced tea.

9!!! I've been to the Loving Hut in Oklahoma City, San Francisco, Los Angeles, Dallas, Falls Church, Cincinnati ... but, Williamsburg / Brooklyn is still the best. Edit; add Atlanta (omg!) & Orlando. Someday, I hope to go to the LH in Hanoi.

Actual review is 3.5 stars.  The food is a little better than the rating would imply:  the sauce with the samosa appetizer was incredible, the samosas themselves were good, and the pesto pasta was fine.  The prices were not a great value but were perfectly reasonable.  The ambience is also nice at the restaurant, but service was unbelievably slow at dinner time given there were only three other tables in the restaurant.  I never want to rush the kitchen but they actually lost my order and had to ask me again to re-make the items I requested.  I might return for the lunch specials, but I wouldn't feel any need to head back and pay the prices one would around dinnertime.
Amazing food.

There’s something here for everyone! Great service (hey Matt and Lisa!), delicious food, accessible prices, and all around good vegan vibes. Apparently they have monthly music events on Saturday too. Looking forward to becoming a regular at this place :)

Tasty, inexpensive, and filling vegan eats with Asian tendencies. Get the golden nuggets and the Malaysian curry app and dip away. So good. Wonton soup is light and balanced, with noodles and fresh veggies in it. "Sea protein" - soy chicken wrapped in nori seaweed - is really yummy and the "seafood" platter is a very solid main.

Amazing vegan food, my partner and I had the General Tso's, Miso Soup, Wonton Soup, Curry Udon Noodles, and the Drumsticks. The General Tso's had a bit of a sweet in a baked good sort of way but still pleasantly savory with an enjoyable crunch. The Miso and Wonton soup were exactly as one would hope. The Curry Udon Noodles were flavorful and a real must-have. The drumsticks were interesting, they had a sugar cane "bone" with a fluffy interior and a crispy exterior that went amazingly well with the aioli sauce.  The atmosphere was quaint but welcoming with a real strong push towards welcoming the vegan life. Lily, the owner, was a real spark of joy in the experience, my partner and I really loved her from the beginning to the end as she was attentive, kind, and gave us such great service. We really appreciated her assistance in making this a great experience for us.  We will definitely be back!  Thank you so much for lily and the team for making this such a great vegan experience for us and for looking after us.
Drove from Ozone Park to have what i seen my friend post on Instagram. The meal was delicious, the vibe was dope and great staff. Will most definitely be coming back.
Awful. Just ordered 5 items and 3 were wrong. Come on,get it together.  Never again
This was good place. I had there with my sister for lunch. We spend great time. Services was amazing. Staff greeted us very well. Great tea selection. Dessert was delicious. Great food menu.
The food is Very good!

First off, the chicken nuggets are AMAZING. They’re so crispy and tasted delicious. I don’t know what the secret is but omg. I 100% recommend everyone try them. Aside from that, my friends and I also got the chipotle Mac and cheese, facon cheeseburger, and the kung pao entree. My friend wasn’t crazy about his burger but I didn’t try it so I can’t say much about it. However, I did try both the Mac and cheese and the kung pao dish and they were both really good! And the portion sizes were great for the cost.

Absolutely delicious and fills you up so fast. Portions are pretty big and can be shared by two people. Service is always quick and it's never too busy there. Also there's always parking available nearby!

The food was pretty good but the restaurant is a bit dirty and smelly. Also would be wonderful to see the menu get more organized. Hope so much that they remodeled and shape up a bit. I enjoyed the food and support all vegan restaurants.💖💕
Ordered through Postmates canceled order after an hour and a half, then claim the order was never made even though Postmates had a record of it and didn't cancel it.
Absolutely love Loving Hut restaurant. It is the best food of any chain restaurant! Wonderful service and creative menu. I've been to eight of them and Brooklyn is still my favorite.

The waiters were very friendly and always smiling. Great service at good prices. Food is always fresh and in good quality. A fantastic place for lunch or dinner.

Very tasty food, and very affordable. Our server Feiyue was so nice and helpful. He suggested the General Tso's and he was right, it was great. Pretty good size menu with so many vegan choices. Ambiance is non-existent. It looks and feels cheap. But if you need a nice, filling meal at a great price with friendly staff, check out Loving Hut.

Best vegan spot in the neighborhood! Kosher and features gluten and soy-free options, and the most affordable prices I’ve seen for a vegan restaurant in a while. Highly recommend their Rangoons (pictured) and king oyster mushroom appetizer. Will be back a million times and send all the friends.
Loved it! Went a year or so ago. Could definitely revamp their interiors but all over tasty af

We ordered the alfalfa rolls and you could see a receipt rolled up inside the roll through the rice paper wrap. I had to fight with them to get a refund and the owner said it wasn’t fair to give a refund.
Love it

Being traditionally a meat eater living with a vegetarian, I was completely blown out of the water! The sweet and sour delight tasted exactly like sweet and sour chicken, same texture and everything (better than the real thing in this case).  I was very interested in the way the food was prepared and they were more than willing to make recommendations, and were quite friendly in the process. It's 100% worth a shot, vegan or not

Loving hut? More like loving butts! I ordered a few items from their menu and was severely disappointed. All of the vegetables were raw... with a small sauce container of tahini. It was gross. Seriously for the price its way better to just cook at home. Plus, the hot an sour soup was just raw cabbage in a vegetable broth... for $5?! And the roll of rotting salad was just enough to push me over the edge and write a review

Overall I just wish the food had more flavor.

TLDR: hair in food, server was apathetic about the situation, careless towards her tables, just okay food  only leaving a 1 star based on my experience with the server we had. i found a giant hair tangled in my burger so i kindly brought it up to her and let her know that it wasn't a huge deal to me personally but the workers and the kitchen should probably be aware of it so it doesn't happen again to someone who does think it's a big deal. she was incredibly apathetic about it and basically shrugged her shoulders. never brought it up again, never had a manager come over, never offered to comp part of the burger, or even offer a complimentary dessert-- she just didn't do ANY sort of gesture to acknowledge the situation. it wasn't busy, she had maybe 6 tables total so it was especially weird that she dismissed me so quickly. another table told her they wanted to leave because they were waiting so long for their food and she got mad at them??? the food was hit or miss but yeah that server literally did not know what she was doing
Every dish here is so flavorful and fresh. Literally my favorite vegan spot for lunch.

Love this place! It is a very peaceful place with delicious food....
Decent food but great portion sizes.  Could work on food flavor.

I used to eat here about once a week. The menu is extensive, there is wifi and typically enough space to spread out. This place is ideal for vegans and non-vegans, even picky eaters prone to complaining about vegan food :-D  The food is memorably good! My favorite thing is the stuffed eggplant. The bread it comes with is so tasty! The drumsticks, chicken nuggets, and currys are all great. I wasn't a fan of the mac and cheese though.  The vegan donuts from Vegan Treats bakery are worth the trip by themselves. Despite being a chocolate lover, the coconut cream-filled donut is my favorite. They also have kombuha and their housemade tea a treat.  The service is hit or miss unfortunately. The food is fast but the servers could be more friendly and more attentive. Some of them have been wonderful, others on the grumpy side.
First visit, first impression: outstanding. Very friendly and helpful staff, good vibe. Nice place and decor. My first two options were delicious, I luv'em... TBC...
Such good food!! All vegan!! Cute and cozy place with great desserts and Kombucha always. Owner is very involved and is around a lot. Fast takeout services!

Really tasty food and nice atmosphere. Right next to the L line. Also cheap! Service was great!

Delivery was over 20 minutes late. Also I ordered the hummus and taro chips and the taro chips were substituted with processed dorito like chips that were stale. Will not be ordering again.

They always forget something in my order and have failed to replace or return my money multiple times. The food is good enough, but the service is terrible. Wait time for delivery usually takes an hour and a half, sometimes two.
Amazing vegan food.
100 percent vegan and delicious

First time there. Food was really good. Had the BBQ seitan with fried rice. Soooo good. Also had the crispy ragoon as an appetizer that was great. Food and service was good. They should serve the ragoon in a small bowl instead of a big plate. Decor can use some work. But was there for the food. And was not disappointed.
Super tasty and so much food!

The food was poor quality, not well cooked, and over all disappointing. I would not return.

Amazing, as a vegan for 3.5 years, some of the food they offer scared me in it's realistic recreation 😂. The "shrimp" looked identical to real shrimp and everything was phenomenal! I couldn't believe it! Please go!
This place was fantastic! I got a delicious vegan and gluten free meal for $8! I'm so happy!!!

I have heard about this place many times. I have also heard the story of the founder so I had high hopes for this place and came with the expectation of having a memorable experience. That was shattered very quickly.  First off let me just mention before I forget because this irks me. The 15% off 25.00 or more and the 5% off from check-ins...will not be honored.  Sooo, I bring my girlfriend and her mother here to eat. From the all the great things I hear, I did not expect it to look (as another reviewer commented) as if it has not been updated since 1990. I myself would say closer to 1985. This in itself could be forgiven as I am the first to run into the grimiest looking places in other countries if I hear the food is good. However, you must, first of all, have good food and second at least try to have some type of decent customer service.  Let's go with that last part there that truly made this a visit that I would much rather forget. This waitress (holding back using additional adjectives here) must have been the worst I have ever encountered. In my rush to leave, I did not get the name. Note to staff: this occurred 10/09/2019 around 5:00. She was not only rude but a bit confrontational and downright disrespectful. I was holding my tongue due to the fact of being in the company of my girlfriends' mother. The same goes for her because I could see my girlfriend was about to lose it. I'll end that here as she deserves no more of my attention. Good luck with your short-lived service industry position.  As for the food. Blah. Well, let me take that back as we ordered different menu items and two of them were good. The first being some type of alfredo pesto noodle. Not a hard dish to make but I'll give credit where its due. The next tasty item was the Rainbow Soy Wrap. The second place I've tried from and I'm a fan but would not be ordering from here again.  Here is something I've never encountered before. No option for anything to drink but water and hot tea! What? At a restaurant, c'mon. Well thats not entirely true. My girlfriend and I had the "last two" cold Thai Tea drinks according to the waitress. Her mother tried to order one shortly after us and found out the only option was water or hot tea. And as far as the hot tea is concerned. The waitress seemed a bit confused about that one as well so maybe there was only water.  I am really at a loss for words on this one and I shouldn't be as it was one of the worst experiences I ever had dining out. It just made it so much more uncomfortable because I was holding my tongue due to company and wanting to get up and leave the entire time but not wanting to do that to my guests.  Too bad I did not charge this one on the AMEX because it would be the first time ever disputing a meal out. lol. Honestly, this was uncomfortable and a terrible experience. My girl was also disgusted, this being after she has come here multiple times and recomended it.
Best vegan restaurant highly recommended
Amazing food great service and good location, try the combination of edamame with mint and ranch sauce it taste really delicious
Best vegan restaurant I've ever been to. And I'm not vegan. Great customer service but the food.....the food!!!!
Food can be hit or miss, but mostly it's good.
Great pan-asian food. Relatively inexpensive.
Great portions, great flavours. Nice staff and lovely place.

Been here a couple of times now and again, it didn't fail to disappoint. You get huge servings and there's such a chill, homely vibe to the joint. Love going to a place where it's 100% vegan.. no worries that someone in the kitchen is gonna stuff anything up!
Really good, hearty large meals and wonderful friendly staff who were quick and attentive :)
Wonderful place, delicious vegan food, amazing vegan desserts, and very friendly staff! Service is always quick and food is phenomenal.
Great service and delicious food!

First time visiting loving hut; food was decent. I ordered the Pad Thai and was a little disappointed that there weren't as much veggies as I would've liked. Food portions are generous and the prices aren't bad at all. Not in any rush to return anytime soon.

I been ordering from this place for over a year now.  The service over the past few months has been lacking but since my husband and I always pick up our order I didn’t care too much.  Today, I ordered two spicy mambos with sea protein.  My husband goes to pick up the order and they only give him one rice. When he said there should be two they claimed the dish only needed one rice even through there are two orders! This isn’t the first time this happened. And because they refused to give us what we paid for I refuse to ever spend my money here again.  My husband was able to get the rice we paid for but the owner or whoever was working today asked him if he was happy? The lack of customer service, plus the attitude is enough to keep me away for good.

Most of the food here is good. In fact, it is one of our “go to” restaurants, but the quality is somewhat dependent on the individual chef. I love the curry noodle soup and the kale (I did not love the mac and “cheese” or burgers, but it may have been an off night). We used to order delivery but the food was always late, sometimes the order was incomplete, and the food wasn’t as good. If you’re going to eat in the restaurant (or pick up the food) it’s worth it. If you need delivery, go somewhere else.

We did not love everything that we ordered at the Loving Hut. The appetizers were really good and everyone in the party enjoyed them, but the entreés and soups were lacking in finalized flavor. What I mean by that is, their recipes had good basic flavor, but the creators did not continue tweaking to reach the pinnicle of each dish. In otherwords, the main dishes tasted like something any low skill cook could out together at home. In an area that has low options for vegan café/resturants I do say I would visit once in a while. But the competition is fearce in Brooklyn and Loving Hut does not have what it takes to compete. I hope they take their dishes back to the test kitchen and work the recipes down a few more generations. Find the flavors, Loving Hut, that make our palates sing.
Me and my homie eat here once week. Great service, excellent food, plesanpl atmosphere
The food is really flavorful and unlike many other vegan places they don’t overdo the salt and spice trying to hide lack of flavor.
amazing vegan donuts & lil bites 🙂
